text: Nizhniye Karmaly () is a rural locality (a selo) in Srednekarmalinsky Selsoviet, Yermekeyevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 336 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Yermekeyevo, 5 km from Sredniye Karamaly. == References == Category:Rural localities in Yermekeyevsky District
title: Nizhniye Karmaly
